The '''Republica Galactica''' was the [[Galaxy|galactic]] government brought to an end by trader [[Baron|barons]] and corrupt politicians, heralding the rise of the [[Galactic Empire|First Galactic Empire]].

The Republica was founded with the help of a man named [[The Skywalker]], a hundred thousand years before the Empire.

At its height, it consisted of over a million [[Planet|worlds]]. The leaders of the power and transport guilds suborned the [[Galactic Senate|Great Senate]] as it grew too unwieldy to administer the state. This conspiracy was discovered by the [[Jedi-Bendu|Jedi Bendu]], who were counter-accused of [[Treason|treason]]. Several Jedi were tried and sentenced to [[Death|death]]. Members of the Senate then orchestrated civil disorder and terrorism, spurring popular support for the creation of a police state and later the Empire. The [[Galactic Emperor|Emperor]] himself was a mere puppet.

The [[Holy Rebellion of '06]] saw the fall of the Republica's guardians, the Jedi Bendu of [[Light side of the Force|Ashla]] in a conflict with the [[Knights of Sith|Black Knights of the Sith]]. The Sith became the bodyguard of the Emperor, led by the [[Sith Master|Master of the Sith]].

The last remnants of the Republica fled to the [[Outer Rim Territories|Outlands systems]] and the [[Great Rift]] to escape the tyranny of the Empire.

==Behind the scenes==
The Republica Galactica was a concept introduced in the [[Adventures of the Starkiller, Episode I: The Star Wars|second draft]] of the script for [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']]. It survived into the story synopsis and [[The Star Wars: From The Adventures of Luke Starkiller|third draft]].<ref name="The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film">''[[The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film]]''</ref> The fourth draft renamed it the [[Galactic Republic|Old Republic]].<ref name="ALSTJW">{{WebCite|url=https://www.starwarz.com/starkiller/star-wars-the-adventures-of-luke-starkiller-as-taken-from-the-journal-of-the-whills|text=''The Adventures of Luke Starkiller as taken from the Journal of the Whills: Saga I: The Star Wars'', fourth draft|archivedate=20240518135003}}</ref>

The concept would evolve in [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] and the [[Prequel trilogy]] to be the [[Galactic Republic]]. An intermediate version appears in the [[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|novelization]] of ''A New Hope'', which mentions "the massive organs of commerce" and [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] being a puppet. The involvement of corporate interests reappears in the Prequel trilogy with the [[Trade Federation]] and the factions of the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]].

The nomenclature of ''Republica'' appears in [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] in various contexts associated with the Galactic Republic, such as [[500 Republica/Legends|500 Republica]] and [[Republica House]].

